<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-08T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-08T19:00:00-05:00" n="616" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">851B.20/36a: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Consul General in Martinique (<persName type="to">Malige</persName>)</hi><note n="78" xml:id="d616fn78">On April
                                10, 1942, Mr. Malige was promoted from Consul to Consul General in
                                Martinique.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-08T20:00:00-04:00">May 8,
                                    1942—8 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>92. The French Embassy was requested today to advise Admiral Robert that
                            Admiral Hoover<note n="79" xml:id="d616fn79">Adm. John H. Hoover, U.S.
                                Commander of the Caribbean Sea Front.</note> and Mr. Reber<note n="80" xml:id="d616fn80">Samuel Reber of the Division of European
                                Affairs.</note> are scheduled to arrive at Fort-de-France tomorrow
                            morning, Saturday, May 9, by plane from Puerto Rico for consultation
                            with the High Commissioner.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>